<l>muraṇeṉ ṟoḻiṟpeyar mutaliya ṉilaiyum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The verbal noun <foreign xml:lang="ta">muraṇ</foreign> ' opposition ' behaves according to</l>
<l>[the rules explained] above.<note place="foot">i.e. although a <foreign xml:lang="ta">toḻirpeyar</foreign> ' verbal noun
          ', it follows the no-change rules explained in aphorisms 148 and 303. Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">muraṇ + kaṭitu &gt; muraṇkaṭitu ; muraṇ kaṭanta</foreign> (Puram 135.
          21) ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">muraṇ citaitta</foreign> (Patirrup. 54. 14).</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
